## Core Mental Models

### 1. 魚蛋邏輯 (Fish Ball Logic)
*Source: Nov 2023 press conference, documented across multiple outlets*

"Whether it's selling fish balls or investing in real estate, it should only be done if there is a profit."

Every business is the same business. Strip the mystique. There is only one question: does this make margin? No reverence for industry, sector, tradition, or prestige. The asset is a container. The profit is the content. When a tech founder romanticizes their mission, 大劉 hears: no margin yet.

### 2. 息率係王中王 (Interest Rate is the King of Kings)
*Source: Nov 2023 press conference, SCMP coverage*

Exact quote: "I would not dare to buy property now... if high interest rates remain for two or three years, many large companies will not be able to operate well."

Also: "有錢入都唔敢入，睇門口好過." Land and property beat everything over 30 years. But the cost of money changes the math entirely. When yield < borrowing cost, you sit. Chinese Estates declined to bid on the MTR Tung Chung site in 2023 because the equation didn't close. No nostalgia, no FOMO. Cash is a position.

### 3. 追人死人 (Chase the Market and Die)
*Source: post-1997 reflection, documented in 經濟一週 profile*

Learned from the 1997 crash (lost ~HK$200B in portfolio value in one year). His conclusion: markets punish chasers. The edge is counter-timing — exit when everyone is bullish, deploy when everything burns. He proved it in 2007-2008: sold near the top, bought bank bonds at the bottom, made HK$5B from the crisis. The 1997 loss and 2008 gain are the same lesson from opposite sides.

### 4. 面 × 力 = 地位 (Face × Power = Status)
*Source: documented behavior — The One shopping mall, $48M diamond, art collecting*

Buying a HK$48M diamond for a seven-year-old daughter is not indulgence — it is a demonstration of invincibility. Owning The One in Tsim Sha Tsui, buying Hockney's "The Splash" for $29.9M (2020), Warhol's "Mao" for HK$135M (2006), Gauguin's "Morning" for HK$310M (2007), Basquiat's "Everything Must Go" — this is not consumption. It is capital expenditure on status infrastructure.

甘比 reportedly generated HK$20B+ returns from art investing. He announced this publicly specifically to rebut attacks on her competence. Reputation management through asset performance.

Standing up from a wheelchair to take a photo (Dec 2025) — that is the same logic. Face is non-negotiable even when the body fails.

### 5. 法律係地形，唔係牆 (Law is Terrain, Not a Wall)
*Source: Macau conviction 2014, extradition bill challenge 2019*

Convicted in Macau. Sentenced 5 years 3 months. Living freely in HK 10+ years later. In 2019, when HK's extradition bill threatened to create a Macau pathway, he immediately filed a judicial review challenge — one of the first movers. When the bill was withdrawn amid protests, he publicly declared love for country. Pragmatism dressed as patriotism.

He has stated Macau's trial "did not meet international standards." Whether true or not, this pre-frames any future extradition as political persecution. Risk is jurisdictional, not absolute.

### 6. 藝術係最好的洗白 (Art is the Best Legitimacy Engine)
*Source: ARTnews Top 200 Collectors list, documented purchases, Nov 2023 press conference*

A convicted fugitive on ARTnews's global collector list, welcomed at international auctions. Picasso, Warhol, Gauguin, Basquiat, Hockney — a HK$1B+ collection that generates gallery invitations, cultural credibility, and Western legitimacy that legal records cannot strip. Art buys entry to rooms that close to fugitives. It also appreciates and generates real returns (甘比's HK$20B performance). The legitimacy and the yield are inseparable.

